</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>SB1409:v98#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="SB1409"/><meta name="dc:title" content="SB &#xA;              1409-&#xA;                AMENDED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td align="center"><span style=" text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 1em">
                Amended
               IN </span><span style=" text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 1em">
                Senate
              </span> <span style="text-transform: uppercase">April 09, 2026</span><br/></td></tr></tbody><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Senate Bill
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 1409</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Senator Rubio<br/></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>February 20, 2026</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> An act to<font color="#B30000"><strike> add Chapter 4.5 (commencing with Section 9450) to Part 1 of Division 2 of Title 2 of the Government</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> amend Section 19550 of the Business and Professions</i></font> Code, relating to<font color="#B30000"><strike> the Legislature.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> horse racing.</i></font></span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">SB 1409, as amended, Rubio.
                          <font color="#B30000"><strike>Legislature: bills. </strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>Horse racing: charity days.</i></font></span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Existing law requires each licensed racing association that conducts 14 weeks or less of racing to designate 3 racing days, and each licensed racing association that conducts more than 14 weeks of racing to designate 5 racing days during any one meeting, to be conducted as charity days for the purpose of distributing the net proceeds to beneficiaries.</div></i></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill would instead require each licensed racing association that conducts 12 weeks or less of racing to designate 3 racing days, and each licensed racing association that conducts more than 12 weeks of racing to designate 5 racing days during any one meeting, to be conducted as charity days for the
			 purpose of distributing the net proceeds to beneficiaries.</div></i></font><font color="#B30000"><strike><p style="display:inline;"><s>The California Constitution vests the legislative power of the state in the Legislature, which consists of the Senate and Assembly. The Legislature may make law only by the enactment of a statute, and may enact a statute only by bill.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>This bill would require a bill introduced in the Legislature to be assigned a bill number that identifies the applicable legislative session, as provided. The bill would require the Secretary of the Senate, Chief Clerk of the Assembly, and Legislative Counsel Bureau to ensure that all legislative publications, indexes, journals, databases, and electronic
			 systems use and display that bill number.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="vote">
      Vote:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">MAJORITY</span>  </span><span id="appropriation">
      Appropriation:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">YES</span>  </span><span id="localprogram">
      Local Program:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><div id="bill"><div style=" text-transform: uppercase"><h2 style=" text-align: left;">The people of the State of California do enact as follows:</h2><br/></div><div id="s10.3935767665827634"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>SECTION 1.</i></font></h3> <font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>Section 19550 of the Business and Professions Code is amended to read:</i></font></div><div><div id="id_478F2D32-41F4-45F3-B0E1-19E77182B16A"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">19550.</h6> (a) The board shall require each licensed racing association that conducts<font color="#B30000"><strike> 14</strike></font><font color="#B30000"><strike> or less weeks</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> 12 weeks or less</i></font> of racing to designate 3 racing days, and each licensed racing association that conducts more than<font color="#B30000"><strike> 14</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> 12</i></font> weeks of racing to designate five racing days during any one meeting, to be conducted as charity days by the licensee for the purpose of distribution of
						the net proceeds therefrom to beneficiaries through the distributing agent. For<font color="#B30000"><strike> the</strike></font>
						purposes of this section, a split meeting shall be considered a single meeting and the appropriate number of charity days shall be based on the total weeks of racing allocated for both periods of the meeting.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) Notwithstanding subdivision (a) or any other<font color="#B30000"><strike> provision of</strike></font> law,<font color="#B30000"><strike> no</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> a</i></font> racing association shall<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> not</i></font> be required to pay to a distributing agent for the purpose of distribution to beneficiaries more than an amount equal to two-tenths of 1 percent of the association’s total on-track handle on live races conducted by the association at the
						meeting.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(c) This section does not apply to a fair, or to a licensed racing association conducting three weeks of racing or less.</div></p></div></div></div></div><font color="#B30000"><strike><caml:BillSection id="id_181FAE03-955E-4DE6-9BFA-0DF050D1D821"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>SECTION 1.</caml:Num><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>The Legislature finds and declares that the changes to bill numbering required by this act will improve public access, clarity, and transparency in California’s legislative recordkeeping.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:BillSection><caml:BillSection id="id_06910215-1FC6-491B-AA83-BC44362EA7C3"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>SEC. 2.</caml:Num><caml:ActionLine action="IS_ADDED" xlink:href="urn:caml:codes:GOV:caml#xpointer(%2Fcaml%3ALawDoc%2Fcaml%3ACode%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'TITLE'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'2.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'DIVISION'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'2.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'PART'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'1.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'CHAPTER'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'4.5.'%5D)" xlink:label="fractionType: LAW_SPREAD||commencingWith: 9450" xlink:type="locator">Chapter 4.5 (commencing with Section 9450) is added to Part 1 of Division 2 of Title 2 of the <caml:DocName>Government Code</caml:DocName>, to read:</caml:ActionLine><caml:Fragment><caml:LawHeading id="id_92147F26-FB0F-4DFF-BEBE-F93C18AB6B47" type="CHAPTER"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>4.5.</caml:Num><caml:LawHeadingVersion id="id_659926BC-4557-416A-B8C9-48B2D24F3F9F"><caml:LawHeadingText>Naming and Numbering of Bills</caml:LawHeadingText></caml:LawHeadingVersion><caml:LawSection id="id_90A8F67D-A1E7-4764-B032-8D3D1B8D33BD"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>9450.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_559FF398-24D7-4A61-AC50-52FD1E08ED9A"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>(a)<span class="EnSpace"/>Every bill that is introduced in the Legislature shall be assigned a bill number that identifies the legislative session in which the bill is introduced. The legislative session shall precede the name of the house in which the bill was introduced according to the following format:</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(1)<span class="EnSpace"/>For a Senate bill, “[Name of the legislative session]—Senate Bill No. ____,” or “[Name of the legislative session]—SB ____.”</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(2)<span class="EnSpace"/>For an Assembly bill, “[Name of the legislative session]—Assembly Bill No. ____,” or “[Name of the legislative session]—AB ____.”</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(b)<span class="EnSpace"/>In the bill number, the name of the legislative session may be
					 abbreviated, such as “2027–28 Reg. Sess.” or “2027–28 1st Ex. Sess.”</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection><caml:LawSection id="id_6E95AEB1-DF50-4F0E-9ED3-64527A1E4BD4"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>9451.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_E93E1C10-6261-4628-ACAF-E0A7B433828C"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>(a)<span class="EnSpace"/>The Secretary of the Senate, the Chief Clerk of the Assembly, and the Legislative Counsel Bureau shall ensure that all legislative publications, indexes, journals, databases, and electronic systems use and display a bill’s complete number pursuant to Section 9450.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(b)<span class="EnSpace"/>The Secretary of the Senate, the Chief Clerk of the Assembly, and the Legislative Counsel Bureau shall make any necessary technical and conforming changes to legislative systems and materials to implement the requirements of this chapter.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection><caml:LawSection id="id_CE75BAC5-6F08-44C7-9A01-6A68E9EDB7E1"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>9452.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_4EEB6BEE-2CC7-40CD-92E7-0A4E66FEC11C"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>This chapter applies to bills introduced during the 2027–28 Regular Session and any regular session thereafter, and to bills introduced during any special session commencing on or after January 1, 2027.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection></caml:LawHeading></caml:Fragment></caml:BillSection></strike></font></div></div></body></html>
